## Amendment (lint fix folded in)

`as_attributes()` originally returned the `IntegrationAttributes` TypedDict.
That broke CI Python lint (mypy + pyright) across the descendant PRs in this
stack:

- `op(attributes=...)` and `Op.attributes` are typed `dict[str, Any] | None`,
  and a TypedDict is NOT assignable to `dict[str, Any]` (mutable/invariant), so
  `weave.op(attributes=X.as_attributes())` in op-based integrations (bedrock x5,
  notdiamond x2) failed with `call-overload`.
- llamaindex (callbacks PR) stamps a `"weave"` key onto the returned dict, which
  a closed TypedDict rejects (`typeddict-unknown-key` / pyright
  reportGeneralTypeIssues).

Fix: `as_attributes()` now returns `dict[str, Any]`, constructed via the
`IntegrationAttributes`/`IntegrationInfo` TypedDicts (so field/key safety is kept
at construction) and handed out through a single `cast(dict[str, Any], ...)`.
The cast is a runtime no-op, so it avoids the extra dict copy a `{**...}` spread
at every call site would incur, and all call sites stay in their natural
`attributes=X.as_attributes()` form. Folded into this base commit so every
descendant PR inherits the corrected return type after `gt restack`.

Verified with the pinned hooks (ty/pyright/mypy/ruff via prek) — all pass — and
the as_attributes unit tests (value equality + fresh-copy mutation) still pass
since runtime behavior is unchanged.

